data.description: Ideally located in the heart of the Old North End, this exquisite home captures the essence of a bygone era while offering modern updates, comforts, and conveniences. Upgraded and modernized to meet today's lifestyle needs while honoring its heritage. Well-maintained property with recent updates is waiting for you to call it home. With its architectural details, wonderful outdoor space, and proximity to downtown, this property is a true gem. The home's curb appeal is immediately evident with its striking exterior featuring easy-maintenance stucco, newer fencing (2021), and multiple relaxing outdoor spaces in front and back. Step inside to discover a blend of historic elegance and contemporary updates. The main level interior boasts high ceilings, new floors throughout (2023), windows that fill the home with natural light, modernized kitchen with stainless steel appliances (2yrs), quartz countertops (2021), a center island/counter bar (2021), custom-made pantry (2021), and gas range. Also on the main floor are two bedrooms with ample closets, an updated bathroom with contemporary fixtures and double vanity (2022), and a cozy sunroom off the kitchen overlooking the deck -perfect for morning coffee or reading. The upper level offers a large bedroom featuring brand-new carpet, ample closet spaces, and a dedicated desk area to provide a private retreat or versatile space for work or leisure. 2 AC units (3yrs), one for each level. The backyard is a private oasis with a spacious composite deck for outdoor dining and entertaining amid grape vines. The oversized, attached 2-car garage has newer walls and epoxy floors (both 2022). Situated in the Old North End, this home offers the following advantages: A short walk to downtown Colorado Springs with its shops, restaurants, and cultural attractions. Proximity to parks and schools, including Monument Valley Park and Colorado College campus. Easy access to hiking and biking trails in the City and nearby Mountains.
